every morning and night have to choose to take my meds, which prevent intense manic & depressive episodes and the list of issues that come w them. episodes still happen but I've noticed that i'm better equipped to deal with them when medicated

the thing about being mentally ill that I think a lot of people don't understand is that I have to wake up every day and make the decision to be healthy so many times throughout the day, but not in a "i'm gonna have a salad instead of a burger" type way
